abstract = {The purpose of this study is to improve the use of technology for the occurrence of a disaster as a form of anticipation in a disaster-prone area and tourist area. The method used in this research was a descriptive research method where the data obtained from events that occur in a particular region. The results of this study indicate that technological innovation is needed to monitor floods and landslides because based on the data from National Disaster Management Agency (BNPB) on the occurrence of disasters in Indonesia. There are still many areas that prone to natural disasters especially floods and landslides. The important role of the technology is to increase the level of confidence and security of tourists towards the potential for a disaster that occurs and can improve the tourism industry economy.}
